  "title" : "Retrieve only static fields declared in Java class",
  "body" : "<p>I have the following class:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test {\n    public static int a = 0;\n    public int b = 1;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Is it possible to use reflection to get a list of the static fields only? I'm aware I can get an array of all the fields with <code>Test.class.getDeclaredFields()</code>. But it seems there's no way to determine if a <code>Field</code> instance represents a static field or not.</p>\n"
